 Evangelist Ebenezer Obey-Fabiyi, ‘Miliki king,’ is set for celebration on his 80th birth anniversary. Obey, popularly called Chief Commander, would turn 80 on April 3. It was gathered that preparations were being made by family, fans, and associates to celebrate Obey at 80. The Juju music maestro is widely loved for his immense contribution to the music industry in Nigeria and Africa at large. The birthday celebration committee was reported to have said that the congregation of Decross Gospel Mission would host the celebrant who is the General Overseer of the church, alongside his family members, dignitaries and other invited guests in a thanksgiving service, on April 3, at the church headquarters in Lagos. A reception would follow at the Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library event hall, in Abeokuta, Ogun State, on April 8. A classy event would be held at the Eko Hotel and Suites, Lagos, on May 22, by organisers of Headies Awards in celebration of the creativity and the roles of the music icon as a living legend in the industry. The occasion would witness the convergence of both the young and the older generations of artistes, and a new biography of Obey would be launched at the event. 